{"word":"Ἁγάρ","slug":"Ἁγάρ","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b><el>Ἁγάρ, ἡ</el></b> [<a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ Heb.\">Heb.</a>] <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ indecl.\">indecl.</a> <b><i>Hagar,</i></b> Sarah’s slave, loaned to Abraham as a concubine (<a href='B:10 16:1'>Genesis 16</a>), mother of Ishmael, in imagery of the Mosaic code <b><a href='B:550 4:24'>Gal 4:24f</a>.</b> <center id=\"nav_bottom\"> <a id=\"left_arrow\" href=\"S:ἀγαπητός\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> <a id=\"bottom_home\" href=\"S:#1.Table of Contents\">&emsp;&emsp;</a> <a id=\"right_arrow\" href=\"S:ἀγγαρεύω\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> </center> "}]}